This paper is primarily focused on face recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The proposed approach involves using a graph convolutional network, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions segmentation, which is a common task in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper discusses the challenge of complex variations in cluster patterns, which is a topic of interest in cryptography (cs.CR) as well.
